    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9600 AND 9700 SLEEPER AND NON-SLEEPER CABS -
        WINDSHIELD WIPERS (AIR) - AIR WIPER MOTOR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>AIR WIPER MOTOR</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Both air motors are removed from the front of the cab:</para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen windshield washer hose from fitting on the front of the cab. Lift spring loaded
                    latch to unlock, and lift wiper arm assembly from serrated wiper motor shaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600679">Figure 79</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1600679" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1600679" filename="../figg16/g1600679.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 79. Wiper Arm and Blade</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. WIPER BLADE</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. WIPER ARM</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. CAB BODY</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. WINDSHIELD SEAL</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove retainer clip from end of motor shaft and detach serrated driver and rain shield
                    from the shaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove shaft nut, steel washer and leather washer from shaft.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four mounting screws and detach wiper motor access cover from front of cab.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove four mounting screws and detach air motor from cowl bar (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600680">Figure 80</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1600680" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1600680" filename="../figg16/g1600680.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 80. Removing Wiper Motor Assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. MOUNTING BRACKET, MOTOR</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. WIPER MOTOR</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. AIR LINES</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect air lines. Service or replace parts as required (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1600681">Figure 81</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1600681" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1600681" filename="../figg16/g1600681.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 81. Wiper Motor Assembly</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. WIPER BLADE</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. WIPER ARM</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. RETAINER, DRIVER</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. DRIVER (SERRATED)</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. RAIN SHIELD</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. NUT, MOTOR SHAFT</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. STEEL WASHER</callout1>
                        <callout1>8. LEATHER WASHER</callout1>
                        <callout1>9. WIPER MOTOR</callout1>
                        <callout1>10. VALVE, BACK PRESSURE</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach air lines and position air motor and bracket onto the cowl bar. Use four screws
                    to attach the air motor. Tighten until snug.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use four screws to attach the wiper motor access cover to the front of the cab.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place new leather washer and original steel washer (if OK) onto the shaft. Secure with
                    the shaft nut. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16006_87.xml" xrefid="hl1600626">TORQUE CHART
                        <xref refid="hl1600626"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the rain shield and serrated driver onto the shaft. Secure with a retainer clip.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach the wiper arm assembly to the serrated driver and push down into position.
                    Depress spring loaded latch and lock arm onto shaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the windshield washer hose to the fitting on the front of the cab. Make sure the
                    air lines return to their original connections, free of leaks. Also be sure the air line routing is
                    free of kinks or sharp bends that might result in a restricted air flow.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check wiper arm positioning. Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s16006_70.xml" xrefid="hl1600627">ADJUSTMENT
                        <xref refid="hl1600627"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    in this section.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
